rc/infra/container.py-143-        FailureKind taxonomy as the real CLI runners) or real (per-task\nbackend/src/infra/container.py-144-        resolution through the agent registry's runtime_type + provider/model\nbackend/src/infra/container.py-145-        rows). The secret store is passed as a thunk so dry-run never\nbackend/src/infra/container.py-146-        constructs it (it fails closed on a missing ORCHESTRATOR_MASTER_KEY).\"\"\"\nbackend/src/infra/container.py:147:        return build_agent_runner(\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"agent_message","text":"The stage is already authoritative on the task snapshot: `Task.tdd_stage` yields `test_authoring` before a valid bundle and `implementation` afterward, while `ExecutionHandler` independently computes the run role and passes the same snapshot to the runner. I’ll keep the public runner interface unchanged and have the prompt builder use `task.tdd_stage` plus `spec.role`; this preserves contract-less prompts exactly and avoids touching domain code."}}
